Sequence Information.Peptide Name: Temporin-FL (natural AMPs; frog, amphibians, animals; XXA, UCLL1c)
Sequence Information.Source: skin, Boie's wart frog, rice field frog, and Asian grass frog,Fejervary limnocharis,  Asia

Literature Information.Literature: APD analysis reveals this sequence is most similar (77.78%) toTemporin-RN3L: 24%; I: 18%; F: 18%; A: 6%. GRAVY: 1.75; M Wt: 1876.357; Mol formula:  C96H150N18O20; molar extinction coeff: 0.Chemical modification: C-terminal amidation.Activity: Gram+ S. aureus ATCC 6538 or ATCC25923 or MRSA (MIC 6.25-12.5 uM), P. acnes ATCC6919 (MIC 6.25 uM), and B. subtilis CMCC63501 (MIC 6.25 uM), but not Gram- E.coil ATCC25922 (MIC>100 uM), P.aeruginosa ATCC 27853 (MIC>100 uM) and C.albicans CMCC 98001 (MIC >100 uM).Structure: became helical in the presence of membrane-mimetic SDS micelles.Animal model:mouse: Staph infection IP, 2h post treat IP (5 mg/kg), protected mice from sepsis-caused death.
Literature Information.Author: Li J, Liang Y, Su M, Wu J, Chai J, Xiong W, Mo G, Chen X, Xu X. 2023
Literature Information.Title: Characterization of a Novel LTA/LPS-Binding Antimicrobial and Anti-Inflammatory Temporin Peptide from the skin of Fejervary limnocharis (Anura: Ranidae).
